• Mineral Resource Estimate Update:
  • Kokoseb Gold Project MRE increased by 38% to 2.93Moz gold (89Mt at 1.0 g/t Au, 0.50 g/t cut-off).
  • 1.81Moz Au in Indicated category (62% of total MRE).

  • Higher-grade component: 2.07Moz Au at 1.4 g/t Au (0.80 g/t cut-off).

  • Key Implications:

  • Supports upcoming Scoping Study and planned Definitive Feasibility Study (mid-2026).

  • Resource remains open along strike and at depth, with potential for further growth via drilling.

  • Metallurgical Recovery: Confirmed 92% gold recovery from test work.

  • Next Steps: Ongoing drilling with 4 diamond rigs and 1 RC rig; Scoping Study results expected soon.

No capital raising, trading halt, or financial figures requiring immediate action were identified.

Material Information Summary

Quarterly Report (June 2025) Highlights

Financial & Operational Performance
- Record quarterly Group cash flow: $308M ($1,724/oz).
- Record annual Group cash flow: $787M ($1,051/oz).
- Operating mine cash flow: $697M (quarter), $2,288M (year).
- Closing cash balance: $760M (after $220M debt repayment in FY25).
- Gearing reduced to 15% (from 25% at start of FY25).

FY25 Guidance Achieved
- Production: 751koz gold, 76kt copper.
- AISC: $1,572/oz (includes higher royalty costs due to stronger gold prices).

FY26 Guidance Preview
- Production: 710-780koz gold, 70-80kt copper.
- AISC guidance: $1,720–1,880/oz (inflation impact: ~4%).
- Capital investment: $780–980M (~$200M lower than FY25).

Projects
- Mungari mill expansion: Commissioned; commercial production expected 1H FY26.
- Cowal Open Pit Continuation (OPC): Approved; extends mine life to 2042.

Exploration & Growth
- High-grade drilling results at Mungari and Northparkes support resource expansion.

Dividends & Debt
- 24th consecutive dividend paid (7.0 cents/share, 56% DRP participation).
- No debt maturities until July 2026; undrawn $525M revolving credit facility (extended to 2028).

Safety & Sustainability
- TRIF improved to 4.98 (down 35% YoY).

Commodity Prices
- Achieved gold price: $4,996/oz (June quarter).
- Minimal hedging: 50koz gold at A$3,254/oz for FY26; no copper hedging.

Key Dates
- Full FY26 guidance details to be released 13 August 2025 with FY25 results.

Note: Non-material operational details, director names, and legal boilerplate omitted.

Summary of Material Information (ASX Announcement: MGX Acquisition of 50% in Central Tanami Gold Project)

  • Transaction Type: Acquisition of 50% interest in the Central Tanami Gold Project Joint Venture (CTPJV) from Northern Star Resources (ASX: NST).
  • Purchase Price: A$50M (plus adjustments), funded from existing cash reserves (A$460M as of 31 March 2025).
  • Key Assets:
  • 1.6Moz gold Mineral Resource (JORC 2012) across 11 deposits, primarily on granted mining leases.
  • High-grade Groundrush deposit (historically produced 0.6Moz at 4g/t Au).
  • Existing infrastructure: 1.2Mtpa processing plant (non-operational), haul roads, airstrip, camp.
  • Strategic Rationale:
  • Entry into gold sector, complementing iron ore business (Koolan Island nearing end of mine life).
  • Potential development decision within 12-18 months.
  • Transaction Metrics:
  • A$61/oz (based on JORC 2012 resource) vs. peer average of A$174/oz for comparable transactions.
  • Conditions: FIRB approval, land council consent, and waiver of right of first refusal by JV partner Tanami Gold NL (ASX: TAM).

Material Impact: Diversifies MGX into gold, leverages financial strength, and adds a high-potential asset at a competitive valuation.

Material Information Summary (Exploration Update):

  • Project Acquisition:
  • Granite Castle Project acquired as part of a 2024 asset deal with Collins St Convertible Notes Pty Ltd.

  • Includes 2 exploration permits and 1 Mining Development Licence (MDL 2005).

  • Historic Drilling:

  • Over 22,000m drilled across MDL 2005:
    • Granite Castle shear: 255 holes (15,493m).
    • Coronation shear: 54 holes (3,540m).

  • Notable intercepts:

    • Coronation shear (GCRC 596): 3m @ 10 g/t Au, 153ppm Ag (incl. 1m @ 24.9 g/t Au).
    • Granite Castle shear: 2004 JORC resource (details referenced from prior announcements).

  • Exploration Upside:

  • Shear zones extend 1km west and 200m east of drilled areas.

  • 12 additional untested shear zones identified.

  • Next Steps:

  • Fieldwork and historic core resampling to commence in coming months.

  • Planned drilling later in 2025 to upgrade resources to JORC 2012 compliance.

  • Strategic Context:

  • Located 170km west of NMR’s producing Blackjack Operations (gold production commenced July 2025). Potential future feed source for Blackjack plant.

  • Caution:

  • Historic results not compliant with JORC 2012; validation underway.

Omitted: Background details, director commentary, non-material drilling data (Appendix 1), and routine disclaimers.

Material Information Summary

  • Exploration Results:
  • Bouncer South expansion: High-grade gold-antimony mineralisation extended by 90m strike length and 70m surface width. Peak results:
    • 6.53% Sb + 6.44 g/t Au (IRX00088)
    • 6.49% Sb + 1.22 g/t Au (IRX00091)
    • 5.66% Sb + 2.25 g/t Au (IRX00092)
  • Typhoon Prospect: New high-grade hit of 40.02 g/t Au (IRX00045), extending mineralisation 100m northwest.
  • Stacked veins (Typhoon-Hurricane corridor): New assays suggest multi-vein potential (12.29 g/t Au and 3.60 g/t Au).

  • Hurricane South: 69.48 g/t Au (IRX00059) from outcropping quartz, indicating parallel vein potential.

  • Drilling Update:

  • Maiden RC drill program imminent (July 2025); rig secured, pads under construction.

  • Project Significance:

  • Confirms large-scale, multi-phase orogenic gold-antimony system analogous to Macraes/Fosterville.
  • Untested structural corridors suggest further high-grade potential.
